249
00:22:09,930 --> 00:22:12,733
Mr. Tiny?
Back from the other side?

250
00:22:12,766 --> 00:22:16,703
Yes! Just last week he
was at the Council Library,

251
00:22:16,804 --> 00:22:18,906
messing with
the Book of Souls.

252
00:22:18,939 --> 00:22:20,607
He's trying
to destroy us all!

253
00:22:20,641 --> 00:22:23,577
Megalomaniac!
That man's a megalomaniac!

254
00:22:35,322 --> 00:22:39,159
And those murderous,
scumbag Vampaneze,

255
00:22:39,459 --> 00:22:42,396
they're up to something, too,
and it's all connected.

256
00:22:42,529 --> 00:22:44,598
It's all connected.
I can feel it!

257
00:22:44,665 --> 00:22:47,901
Come with me.
We can avenge old Vincent.

258
00:22:48,035 --> 00:22:49,136
Kill us some Vampaneze!

259
00:22:49,236 --> 00:22:50,737
No. I'm sorry.

260
00:22:50,838 --> 00:22:52,673
No? Why?

261
00:22:54,408 --> 00:22:55,776
I'm done fighting.

262
00:22:55,843 --> 00:22:59,279
I left that life for a reason.
I'm just a vaudevillian.

263
00:22:59,379 --> 00:23:01,482
It's a simple life,
and I like it.

264
00:23:03,116 --> 00:23:04,117
Steve.

265
00:23:04,184 --> 00:23:08,188
I know who you are. I know
what you are, Vur Horsten.

266
00:23:09,823 --> 00:23:13,927
Who sent you? The Apocalypse
Monger? The Blood Barons?

267
00:23:14,027 --> 00:23:16,029
No... No one. I... No
one sent me. I just...

268
00:23:16,129 --> 00:23:18,365
I have these vampire books,
and I saw a painting of him

269
00:23:18,532 --> 00:23:20,300
with some girl in,
like, 1819.

270
00:23:20,367 --> 00:23:23,804
It said that she broke up with him
when she found he was a vampire.

271
00:23:25,005 --> 00:23:26,240
Did you hear
that, Gavner?

272
00:23:26,306 --> 00:23:29,276
Missy broke up with me
because I was a vampire.

273
00:23:29,309 --> 00:23:32,446
Funny, I always thought it was
the only thing she liked about me.

274
00:23:32,513 --> 00:23:34,515
Let the kid go.
Let him go.

275
00:23:36,016 --> 00:23:38,619
Now, are you
mentally unfit?

276
00:23:39,219 --> 00:23:42,089
Didn't you hear me
threaten you at the show?

277
00:23:42,189 --> 00:23:44,391
I did.
It was awesome.

278
00:23:45,325 --> 00:23:50,531
You see, I want this. I want
you to make me into a vampire.

279
00:23:51,632 --> 00:23:54,568
I mean, vampires, they
don't take crap from anybody.

280
00:23:54,668 --> 00:23:56,336
They live by their
own set of rules.

281
00:23:56,403 --> 00:23:59,373
It's true they do have their
own rules. We wrote some of them.

282
00:23:59,439 --> 00:24:03,377
Yes, and one of them is
children can't become vampires.

283
00:24:03,410 --> 00:24:04,611
Look, look, blood.

284
00:24:05,746 --> 00:24:06,980
Blood.

285
00:24:07,514 --> 00:24:10,384
You see, Gavner,
blood.

286
00:24:13,187 --> 00:24:15,689
Look, if you
become a vampire,

287
00:24:15,722 --> 00:24:18,592
you have to leave your
friends and your family.

288
00:24:18,692 --> 00:24:21,328
It's deeply depressing.
Trust me.

289
00:24:22,596 --> 00:24:24,364
Now get out of here.

290
00:24:28,969 --> 00:24:31,071
I haven't seen
my dad in years.

291
00:24:33,173 --> 00:24:35,275
My mom is drunk
all the time.

292
00:24:36,677 --> 00:24:38,579
I absolutely hate my life.

293
00:24:40,514 --> 00:24:43,717
I never actually said it
before, but it's the truth.

294
00:24:45,552 --> 00:24:48,522
This is what
I was meant for.

295
00:24:49,923 --> 00:24:51,725
What you're
meant for?

296
00:24:53,827 --> 00:24:56,163
Well, if that's the case,
let's test your blood.

297
00:24:56,196 --> 00:24:57,331
No. No.

298
00:25:03,170 --> 00:25:06,573
Who sent you here?
Your blood tastes of evil.

299
00:25:09,576 --> 00:25:11,612
You can never
be a vampire.

300
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:14,481
What?

301
00:25:14,548 --> 00:25:16,517
I have what, bad blood?

302
00:25:18,085 --> 00:25:20,120
I'm never gonna
forget this.

303
00:25:21,288 --> 00:25:23,824
One day, I promise you,
I will hunt you down.

304
00:25:23,924 --> 00:25:25,159
And what?

305
00:25:27,227 --> 00:25:28,462
Kill me?

306
00:25:29,396 --> 00:25:33,367
Do you know how easily I could
kill you? I could do it tonight.

307
00:25:33,901 --> 00:25:37,104
I could knock you out and
lay you in front of a bus,

308
00:25:37,204 --> 00:25:38,405
and no one
would ever know!

309
00:25:38,438 --> 00:25:42,843
Calm down. Save that stuff for
the enemy. He's just an idiot kid,

310
00:25:42,976 --> 00:25:45,579
who should be
leaving right now

311
00:25:46,547 --> 00:25:48,081
while he still can.

312
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,255
You're out there, man.

313
00:25:56,023 --> 00:25:58,492
All right.
One for the road.

314
00:26:01,161 --> 00:26:02,930
I'm headed back
to the Mountain

315
00:26:02,930 --> 00:26:07,334
to try to convince those old cowards
to stand up against the Vampaneze.

316
00:26:07,367 --> 00:26:11,972
Gavner, if we kill one
of them, it means war.

317
00:26:13,707 --> 00:26:15,609
Wouldn't that
be a shame?

318
00:26:19,847 --> 00:26:21,381
Poor old Vincent.

319
00:26:22,950 --> 00:26:25,486
You've been awfully
quiet under there.

320
00:26:47,875 --> 00:26:49,009
Get in.

321
00:27:10,664 --> 00:27:14,501
Thanks. Thanks,
I really needed a ride.

322
00:27:14,935 --> 00:27:17,638
Oh, absolutely,
absolutely delighted.

323
00:27:21,074 --> 00:27:23,343
Are you the one
known as Steve?

324
00:27:24,845 --> 00:27:28,949
No, I'm the one
known as Darren.

325
00:27:29,082 --> 00:27:31,318
I actually had a bike.

326
00:27:31,351 --> 00:27:34,655
But I'll just get it
tomorrow in the daylight.

327
00:27:35,155 --> 00:27:38,125
No need.
It's in the trunk.

328
00:27:38,625 --> 00:27:42,362
Now, if I
may ask, Darren,

329
00:27:43,564 --> 00:27:48,368
do you believe in the
immutability of the human soul?

330
00:27:50,304 --> 00:27:51,472
The what?

331
00:27:51,538 --> 00:27:54,541
So, he knows nothing
of souls, does he?

332
00:27:55,375 --> 00:27:57,911
Knows only
of blood, huh?

333
00:27:58,045 --> 00:28:01,982
The pulsing, the
delicious, the ruby red.

334
00:28:08,856 --> 00:28:12,626
Wow, wow, you know what? You
can just let me off right here.

335
00:28:13,227 --> 00:28:14,728
What's the rush?

336
00:28:14,761 --> 00:28:19,333
After all, didn't we save you
from the scary, scary vampire?

337
00:28:22,269 --> 00:28:25,873
Doesn't act like
leadership material.

338
00:28:26,039 --> 00:28:29,409
Acts more like a bag
of blood. Are you? Huh?

339
00:28:29,543 --> 00:28:30,611
Bag of blood?

340
00:28:30,677 --> 00:28:32,880
Shows how much
you know, Murlaugh.

341
00:28:32,980 --> 00:28:35,482
I think he reeks
of potential.

342
00:28:36,250 --> 00:28:37,918
Ow!
Sorry.

343
00:28:39,386 --> 00:28:40,621
Souvenir.

344
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:49,429
We all have
a destiny, Darren.

345
00:28:49,530 --> 00:28:53,100
And with a few simple tests,
we can find out what yours is.

346
00:28:55,302 --> 00:28:57,404
Wonderful to
meet you, Darren.

347
00:28:58,172 --> 00:29:01,041
It's like looking
in a mirror.

348
00:29:11,485 --> 00:29:12,653
Darren!

349
00:29:13,620 --> 00:29:15,289
We'll be in touch.

350
00:29:34,408 --> 00:29:37,177
Freaky dream.
Freaky. Freaky.

351
00:29:43,317 --> 00:29:46,320
Hey. Hey, I'm gonna try
to get you some food, okay?

352
00:29:46,386 --> 00:29:50,057
Just hold on one sec. I'm gonna go get
some flies from the window sill, okay?

353
00:29:50,190 --> 00:29:52,726
Hey. Why have you
been acting so weird?

354
00:29:54,862 --> 00:29:55,996
I'm not acting weird.

355
00:29:56,063 --> 00:29:56,997
You were just talking
to your backpack.

356
00:29:57,097 --> 00:29:58,098
What?

357
00:29:58,132 --> 00:29:59,833
No, I wasn't.
Darren, yes, you were.

358
00:29:59,900 --> 00:30:01,568
I wasn't. Let me... Just
let me see it a second.

359
00:30:01,635 --> 00:30:03,270
You see? It's just my
backpack. Seriously, stop it.

360
00:30:03,470 --> 00:30:05,606
Hey, give me my backpack,
man. Hey, just let me see it.

361
00:30:08,008 --> 00:30:09,943
Holy shit! That's...
That's the...

362
00:30:09,977 --> 00:30:13,247
Yeah, I went back to the theater after
the show and I kind of borrowed it.

363
00:30:13,413 --> 00:30:16,083
You stole from a vampire? Do
you realize you're a dead man?

364
00:30:16,116 --> 00:30:17,317
Shh!
You're a dead man!

365
00:30:17,451 --> 00:30:18,719
He's never gonna find me.

366
00:30:18,819 --> 00:30:20,187
Okay, just...

367
00:30:20,954 --> 00:30:24,625
Wait a second. When did you
go to Vur Horsten's room,

368
00:30:24,758 --> 00:30:26,493
and what did you see?

369
00:30:29,730 --> 00:30:31,331
All right,
I saw everything.

370
00:30:31,498 --> 00:30:34,034
Steve, are you crazy? Why would
you want to become a vampire?

371
00:30:34,067 --> 00:30:37,805
Listen, you can't understand.
You have everything.

372
00:30:38,672 --> 00:30:41,575
What do I have?
A secret best friend?

373
00:30:45,879 --> 00:30:47,080
Hey, leave it
in there, okay?

374
00:30:47,181 --> 00:30:48,515
It's fine.
I want to see it.

375
00:30:48,582 --> 00:30:53,921
Be careful. Hey, be careful,
okay? Be really careful.

376
00:30:57,391 --> 00:31:00,160
This thing's even
more hideous close up.

377
00:31:00,260 --> 00:31:01,261
Can you just put it
back now, please?

378
00:31:15,542 --> 00:31:17,377
Okay,
I need the pipe.

379
00:31:18,846 --> 00:31:20,914
GIRL: I got a B-minus
in history.

380
00:31:21,882 --> 00:31:22,850
No!

381
00:31:25,819 --> 00:31:27,488
Oh, my gosh,
what is that?

382
00:31:40,734 --> 00:31:41,768
Move!

383
00:31:41,902 --> 00:31:42,936
Steve! Wait!

384
00:31:43,670 --> 00:31:45,038
What's going on?

385
00:31:57,184 --> 00:31:59,520
Move! Get out of
the way, idiots!

386
00:32:01,622 --> 00:32:04,625
Watch out! Move!

387
00:32:05,726 --> 00:32:07,327
Hey! Steve, don't!

388
00:32:09,596 --> 00:32:11,999
Now I got you!
Hold still!

389
00:32:13,133 --> 00:32:16,203
What's the matter with you?
Whose side are you on?

390
00:32:22,442 --> 00:32:24,845
Hey! No! Hey!

391
00:32:35,222 --> 00:32:37,458
GIRL: Guys, look,
it's in his shirt!

392
00:32:41,462 --> 00:32:42,563
Get it off me!

393
00:32:42,696 --> 00:32:44,097
GIRL: Oh, my God!

394
00:33:22,269 --> 00:33:25,639
So what have you come to
steal from me this time? Thief!

395
00:33:26,206 --> 00:33:28,142
Nothing. Nothing.

396
00:33:28,242 --> 00:33:33,046
Look, Octa bit my best friend,
Steve, and he's in the hospital,

397
00:33:33,447 --> 00:33:35,215
in a coma,
because of me.

398
00:33:35,249 --> 00:33:38,252
And I was wondering
if you had an antidote.

399
00:33:38,285 --> 00:33:39,620
I do.

400
00:33:39,653 --> 00:33:40,754
Thank you.

401
00:33:40,821 --> 00:33:43,257
But I only have
a couple doses left.

402
00:33:43,323 --> 00:33:46,727
Why should I waste any
on some little psychopath?

403
00:33:46,794 --> 00:33:48,829
Please, I'm begging
you, okay?

404
00:33:48,862 --> 00:33:51,231
Look, I'm really sorry
I stole Octa.

405
00:33:51,899 --> 00:33:54,768
I don't know what came over
me. I never steal things.

406
00:33:55,135 --> 00:33:56,303
Why not?

407
00:33:57,204 --> 00:33:58,205
Because it's wrong.

408
00:33:58,238 --> 00:34:00,507
So then you've learned
a valuable moral lesson.

409
00:34:00,541 --> 00:34:01,508
Yes, I have.

410
00:34:01,642 --> 00:34:04,978
And you'll never do anything
wrong again, as long as you live.

411
00:34:05,145 --> 00:34:06,146
No, I won't.

412
00:34:06,313 --> 00:34:09,383
You see? Now you're
a thief and a liar.

413
00:34:09,449 --> 00:34:11,919
What did
Mr. Tiny want?

414
00:34:12,519 --> 00:34:13,487
Mr. Tiny?

415
00:34:13,587 --> 00:34:15,222
The fat man
in the limousine!

416
00:34:17,057 --> 00:34:20,394
I don't know, something about
souls and... And destiny.

417
00:34:21,094 --> 00:34:22,095
And he knew
where I lived.

418
00:34:22,095 --> 00:34:25,766
Looks like you're in deep
shit, my larcenous friend.

419
00:34:25,866 --> 00:34:29,136
Mr. Tiny doesn't just take
a random interest in people.

420
00:34:29,236 --> 00:34:33,140
And the people he does take an
interest in wind up dead or worse.

421
00:34:37,211 --> 00:34:39,146
What's worse than dead?

422
00:34:40,547 --> 00:34:41,515
Oh.

423
00:34:42,416 --> 00:34:43,884
Lots of things.

424
00:34:48,355 --> 00:34:52,593
All right. I'll do it.
I'll make you a bargain.

425
00:34:53,861 --> 00:34:57,264
You'll become my assistant. I'll
turn you into a half vampire.

426
00:34:57,297 --> 00:35:00,467
You'll be able to go out in the
daylight, very useful for me.

427
00:35:00,501 --> 00:35:03,804
You'll do chores for me and
guard my coffin on the road.

428
00:35:03,871 --> 00:35:07,474
And in return, I'll try and
keep Mr. Tiny away from you.

429
00:35:07,508 --> 00:35:10,377
Oh, and I'll save
your stupid friend Steve,

430
00:35:10,410 --> 00:35:13,413
despite the fact that
he threatened to kill me.

431
00:35:18,118 --> 00:35:19,219
You'll save Steve?

432
00:35:19,253 --> 00:35:20,287
Why not?

433
00:35:24,158 --> 00:35:28,195
If I became a half vampire,
would I have to kill people?

434
00:35:29,363 --> 00:35:30,864
Interested, huh?

435
00:35:31,565 --> 00:35:35,502
Vampires don't kill the people
they feed on. Vampaneze do.

436
00:35:35,569 --> 00:35:39,439
Big source of controversy, war
for about 80 years, then a truce,

437
00:35:39,506 --> 00:35:42,576
getting ugly again,
apparently. But time's wasting.

438
00:35:45,979 --> 00:35:47,915
Want to become a vampire?

439
00:35:48,982 --> 00:35:52,352
It's a lonely life,
but there's lots of it.

440
00:35:53,220 --> 00:35:55,656
I can't make that
decision right now.

441
00:35:58,392 --> 00:36:01,261
Do you wanna go home and
ask your mommy and daddy?

442
00:36:01,328 --> 00:36:04,998
Do they make all the decisions
for good little boys like you?

443
00:36:05,332 --> 00:36:06,767
No, they don't.

444
00:36:09,336 --> 00:36:11,905
Poor Steve doesn't
have much time left.

445
00:36:18,879 --> 00:36:23,217
Fine, I'll do it. To save my
friend, not for any other reason.

446
00:36:24,351 --> 00:36:25,786
So get the antidote.

447
00:36:25,853 --> 00:36:27,087
Right here.

448
00:36:29,189 --> 00:36:31,091
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

449
00:36:31,191 --> 00:36:32,359
First things first.

450
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:35,329
Let's test your blood.

451
00:36:36,864 --> 00:36:39,967
What are you doing? I'm not gonna bite you
in the jugular. I could kill you that way.

452
00:36:40,033 --> 00:36:41,668
Show me your hands.

453
00:36:45,372 --> 00:36:46,340
Ow!

454
00:36:47,241 --> 00:36:48,208
Mmm.

455
00:36:48,942 --> 00:36:52,880
You have good blood. This will
work. All right, hold up your hands.

456
00:36:53,046 --> 00:36:54,982
We're going
to exchange blood.

457
00:36:55,048 --> 00:36:56,150
That's creepy.

458
00:36:56,216 --> 00:36:58,552
I know. But that's
how it's done.

459
00:37:08,695 --> 00:37:11,365
This may hurt when
it gets to your heart.

460
00:37:24,278 --> 00:37:25,646
I feel cold.

461
00:37:27,481 --> 00:37:29,016
Lick your fingers.

462
00:37:38,725 --> 00:37:41,895
Whoa, is that like vampire
power? Do I have super-spit now?

463
00:37:42,029 --> 00:37:45,399
Yes, you have super-spit.
The rest will take a while.

464
00:37:47,634 --> 00:37:49,169
The rest of what?
What will I be able to do?

465
00:37:49,269 --> 00:37:50,904
Can I, like, turn into a bat and stuff?

466
00:37:50,938 --> 00:37:52,873
No, that's bullshit.

467
00:37:53,807 --> 00:37:56,443
Now hop on my back.
We're going to flit.

468
00:37:56,844 --> 00:37:57,778
We're gonna what?

469
00:37:57,878 --> 00:38:00,113
Just shut up
and hop on my back.

470
00:38:11,024 --> 00:38:13,427
You held your
breath, right?

471
00:38:13,560 --> 00:38:15,662
Did I not tell you
to hold your breath?

472
00:38:15,796 --> 00:38:16,997
Oh...

473
00:38:17,030 --> 00:38:18,132
Sorry.

474
00:38:23,337 --> 00:38:24,872
Hold on.

475
00:38:24,938 --> 00:38:26,974
Why didn't we just
take the elevator?

476
00:38:27,074 --> 00:38:28,976
I get claustrophobic.

477
00:38:29,076 --> 00:38:31,778
Strange, huh, given
where I sleep every night.

478
00:38:31,812 --> 00:38:35,415
But somehow when it's my own
confined space, it's different.

479
00:38:36,483 --> 00:38:39,887
He looks horrible. Can you
give him the antidote, please?

480
00:38:44,358 --> 00:38:46,360
She really
didn't like him.

481
00:38:48,996 --> 00:38:50,364
Be careful.

482
00:39:00,474 --> 00:39:02,376
Hey, what are you doing?

483
00:39:05,979 --> 00:39:06,947
Shh.

484
00:39:18,025 --> 00:39:20,194
That's it, right?
He's gonna be better now?

485
00:39:20,294 --> 00:39:21,261
That's it.

486
00:39:29,636 --> 00:39:30,838
You are insufferable.

487
00:39:30,838 --> 00:39:32,206
Back! Stay back!

488
00:39:32,272 --> 00:39:33,240
Code blue...

489
00:39:33,307 --> 00:39:36,143
You have no idea how
ridiculous you look right now.

490
00:39:36,176 --> 00:39:37,277
Code blue...

491
00:39:37,377 --> 00:39:40,314
All right. If you want to pretend
this isn't happening, fine.

492
00:39:40,447 --> 00:39:43,584
But being a vampire takes
skill. What is a code blue?

493
00:39:43,684 --> 00:39:45,185
Code blue, code blue...

494
00:39:45,252 --> 00:39:47,821
Try not to do something
stupid like kill your family.

495
00:39:47,888 --> 00:39:50,924
Code blue, code blue,
room 519, stat.

