01:17:51,271 --> 01:17:54,808
And when I finally die,
I plan on staying dead.

983
01:17:56,076 --> 01:18:00,380
Life may be meaningless, but
death I still have hope for.

984
01:18:01,548 --> 01:18:03,784
Life isn't
meaningless.

985
01:18:03,817 --> 01:18:07,855
Tell me that after 200 years
of it, kid. Good day.

986
01:18:17,731 --> 01:18:18,832
You know
I never liked him.

987
01:18:18,899 --> 01:18:19,967
I never did,
either.

988
01:18:20,134 --> 01:18:21,769
I told you
when I first saw him.

989
01:18:21,902 --> 01:18:23,504
Should never
have let him in.

990
01:18:23,537 --> 01:18:24,772
We all know
it's his fault.

991
01:18:24,938 --> 01:18:28,075
I just can't believe he has the
nerve to walk around in here.

992
01:18:28,175 --> 01:18:29,777
That poor Rebecca.

993
01:18:33,947 --> 01:18:37,451
They took her?
Where?

994
01:18:38,452 --> 01:18:43,323
I don't know, but they said
to tell you to come home.

995
01:18:45,292 --> 01:18:49,897
Which, of course, you're not gonna
do. Wait, Darren, Darren. No, buddy.

996
01:18:49,897 --> 01:18:51,098
Those guys are huge, man.

997
01:18:57,771 --> 01:19:00,007
Hey, Mr. and Mrs. Shan.
Hey, Annie.

998
01:19:00,140 --> 01:19:02,042
Steve. What are
you doing here?

999
01:19:02,609 --> 01:19:07,347
Well, you know, I've been thinking.
You guys probably really miss your son.

1000
01:19:07,381 --> 01:19:11,718
And my mom is drunk half the time, so
she doesn't really notice I'm there.

1001
01:19:12,586 --> 01:19:15,089
How about you
guys adopt me?

1002
01:19:18,258 --> 01:19:19,626
No interest?

1003
01:19:20,961 --> 01:19:23,297
Told you they
wouldn't go for it.

1004
01:19:24,098 --> 01:19:25,065
Hmm.

1005
01:19:25,566 --> 01:19:27,167
How disappointing.

1006
01:19:27,901 --> 01:19:32,306
So few "people" have the
parenting instinct the way I do.

1007
01:19:37,878 --> 01:19:39,546
Ready for the prom?

1008
01:19:51,125 --> 01:19:54,728
Make new friends,
but keep the old

1009
01:19:54,762 --> 01:19:58,031
One is silver
and the other's gold

1010
01:19:58,098 --> 01:20:02,202
Make new friends,
but keep the old

1011
01:20:02,236 --> 01:20:05,472
One is silver
and the other's gold

1012
01:20:55,556 --> 01:20:59,793
Hey, Octa. Say goodbye
to Crepsley for me, okay?

1013
01:20:59,860 --> 01:21:02,062
Tell him I'm sorry
but I have to go home.

1014
01:21:06,800 --> 01:21:09,002
It's time, isn't it?

1015
01:21:30,624 --> 01:21:34,261
Twenty-six.
Twenty-seven, 27.

1016
01:21:34,395 --> 01:21:35,562
Twenty-seven.

1017
01:21:35,763 --> 01:21:38,232
All right, no, no.
Twenty-eight.

1018
01:21:38,265 --> 01:21:40,067
May I borrow
a couple of these?

1019
01:21:42,302 --> 01:21:45,172
Don't forget to bring them
back, though. Both of them.

1020
01:21:45,906 --> 01:21:48,776
You're in danger,
terrible danger.

1021
01:21:48,842 --> 01:21:51,078
Your life and soul
are in jeopardy.

1022
01:21:52,980 --> 01:21:53,947
What did I say?

1023
01:21:54,081 --> 01:21:55,282
Nothing. Something
about the weather.

1024
01:21:55,349 --> 01:21:58,752
Chance of thunderstorms tomorrow.
Don't worry. I'll stay indoors.

1025
01:22:29,516 --> 01:22:32,052
Applause! Applause!

1026
01:22:34,688 --> 01:22:37,658
Look. Little vampire.

1027
01:22:39,493 --> 01:22:40,694
Take a bow.

1028
01:22:40,994 --> 01:22:42,763
Where are my family
and my friends?

1029
01:22:42,796 --> 01:22:43,831
Please.

1030
01:22:43,864 --> 01:22:47,434
Must have patience.
Will spoil the show.

1031
01:22:52,506 --> 01:22:55,375
Do you like? Does Murlaugh have talent?

1032
01:22:56,510 --> 01:22:59,246
No? What do you
know about talent?

1033
01:23:01,381 --> 01:23:06,920
Where is Crepsley?

1034
01:23:09,223 --> 01:23:11,658
Too bad for Crapsley.

1035
01:23:11,725 --> 01:23:15,162
Because he will
miss the show!

1036
01:23:16,663 --> 01:23:21,335
Here is freak all
wrapped up tight.

1037
01:23:23,670 --> 01:23:29,143
And here are beloved family
members. Applause. Applause.

1038
01:23:31,578 --> 01:23:35,149
Hello, beloved son.
Hello, loving parents.

1039
01:23:35,182 --> 01:23:39,720
Hello, cute little sister.
Four bags of blood.

1040
01:23:41,155 --> 01:23:42,589
Don't worry.
You're all gonna be okay.

1041
01:23:42,656 --> 01:23:44,892
Will be better than okay.

1042
01:23:45,626 --> 01:23:48,996
Will be delicious!

1043
01:23:50,531 --> 01:23:52,833
But now, may I present

1044
01:23:53,000 --> 01:23:56,270
reunion with oldest friend
and blood brother,

1045
01:23:56,336 --> 01:23:59,473
with he that shall
one day rule us all,

1046
01:23:59,573 --> 01:24:04,044
the one known as Steve.

1047
01:24:05,245 --> 01:24:07,281
Thank you!
Thank you!

1048
01:24:08,882 --> 01:24:10,150
Steve.

1049
01:24:10,684 --> 01:24:11,885
You're alive?

1050
01:24:13,821 --> 01:24:16,690
You know, that was really an
asshole thing for you to do.

1051
01:24:16,690 --> 01:24:19,960
Make your whole family and your
secret best friend go through all that?

1052
01:24:20,094 --> 01:24:22,529
Look, I didn't mean
to hurt anybody, okay?

1053
01:24:22,629 --> 01:24:24,364
Who cares what
you meant to do?

1054
01:24:24,398 --> 01:24:27,434
What you did was take my
place. That was my dream.

1055
01:24:29,136 --> 01:24:31,438
Steve, what are
you doing with him?

1056
01:24:31,472 --> 01:24:33,407
Who? Murlaugh?

1057
01:24:33,807 --> 01:24:36,143
Come on, man, he's
not as bad as he looks.

1058
01:24:36,143 --> 01:24:39,079
You know, for one thing, he didn't
say I had bad blood like Crepsley.

1059
01:24:39,179 --> 01:24:41,381
And for another thing,
he didn't lie to me.

1060
01:24:41,482 --> 01:24:43,984
And you know what?
They think I'm awesome.

1061
01:24:44,118 --> 01:24:48,188
They say I have a destiny,
or whatever. Look at you.

1062
01:24:49,223 --> 01:24:52,593
Who wants to be a vampire
anyways? Vampires suck.

1063
01:24:52,826 --> 01:24:54,294
Vampaneze rule!

1064
01:24:54,528 --> 01:24:56,029
Juicy!

1065
01:24:56,163 --> 01:24:58,832
First guy I killed,
Mr. Kersey.

1066
01:24:58,866 --> 01:25:01,802
Blood just gets me going,
you know what I mean?

1067
01:25:03,670 --> 01:25:05,739
I wouldn't know. I
haven't been drinking any.

1068
01:25:07,174 --> 01:25:11,578
I know you. Always trying to look
like Mr. Goody-Two-Shoes all the time.

1069
01:25:12,312 --> 01:25:14,281
I bet you'll, like,
resist drinking blood

1070
01:25:14,314 --> 01:25:16,016
and resist drinking
and resist drinking it,

1071
01:25:16,083 --> 01:25:18,852
at the last second become
this total bloodhound!

1072
01:25:20,921 --> 01:25:22,289
All right, man,
here's the deal.

1073
01:25:22,356 --> 01:25:25,559
See, the fat guy, he still wants you on
the team, and despite everything else,

1074
01:25:25,592 --> 01:25:28,429
you are still my best friend.
So I'll tell you what,

1075
01:25:28,495 --> 01:25:31,498
I'll make you a deal that
might just save your ass.

1076
01:25:31,598 --> 01:25:33,901
If you kill your family,
I'll let the freak go.

1077
01:25:35,736 --> 01:25:38,005
Wait. My bad,
that's backwards.

1078
01:25:38,038 --> 01:25:40,507
If you kill the freak,
I'll let your family live.

1079
01:25:40,541 --> 01:25:43,010
What? Let the
juicy one go?

1080
01:25:43,243 --> 01:25:46,647
Hey, look, man, it's part of
the plan. Talk to Mr. Tiny.

1081
01:25:48,282 --> 01:25:49,950
So what do you say?

1082
01:25:50,150 --> 01:25:53,253
Just kill her. Oh, yeah, you
got to drink her blood, too.

1083
01:25:53,721 --> 01:25:55,756
You can do her in
with this.

1084
01:26:21,648 --> 01:26:23,484
MR. TINY: Wait!

1085
01:26:25,519 --> 01:26:27,688
Allow him in,
gentlemen.

1086
01:26:28,889 --> 01:26:30,824
I want to see
this play out.

1087
01:26:31,959 --> 01:26:36,163
Man, that was pathetic. You're
totally weak. You need some blood.

1088
01:26:39,199 --> 01:26:40,467
Murlaugh.

1089
01:26:40,601 --> 01:26:41,635
Finally.

1090
01:26:45,406 --> 01:26:47,374
And we thought you
weren't gonna show.

1091
01:27:41,128 --> 01:27:43,063
I hate spiders!

1092
01:28:01,648 --> 01:28:02,916
Darren. Come here.

1093
01:28:04,985 --> 01:28:06,120
Okay.

1094
01:28:09,890 --> 01:28:11,392
Is that your tail?

1095
01:28:11,525 --> 01:28:12,760
Well, yeah.

1096
01:28:12,993 --> 01:28:15,262
I'm really sorry I got you
involved in this, okay? I...

1097
01:28:15,329 --> 01:28:18,599
Please stop staring.
So you really need blood?

1098
01:28:19,566 --> 01:28:21,001
Yeah.
All right.

1099
01:28:22,236 --> 01:28:25,305
Can you just take
a little? Go ahead.

1100
01:28:26,073 --> 01:28:27,574
I'm offering it to you.

1101
01:28:29,143 --> 01:28:32,813
Thanks. But I just
can't lose it.

1102
01:28:32,846 --> 01:28:33,781
What?

1103
01:28:34,248 --> 01:28:36,517
Whatever's still
making me human.

1104
01:28:37,184 --> 01:28:42,222
Darren, being human's not about
what you are. It's about who you are.

1105
01:29:23,964 --> 01:29:24,965
No.

1106
01:30:11,378 --> 01:30:12,613
He's all yours, lad.

1107
01:30:32,266 --> 01:30:34,968
Good.
Right in the heart.

1108
01:30:36,703 --> 01:30:39,540
So fair and foul a day
I have not seen.

1109
01:30:43,077 --> 01:30:45,646
My people aren't
weak like yours.

1110
01:30:46,647 --> 01:30:48,816
They will avenge me,
Crepsley.

1111
01:30:54,188 --> 01:30:58,992
The truce, 100 years,
is over.

1112
01:31:01,161 --> 01:31:03,063
The war begins.

1113
01:31:11,872 --> 01:31:14,875
Marvelous. Magnificent.

1114
01:31:14,908 --> 01:31:19,313
Really. Bravo. Bravo.

1115
01:31:19,713 --> 01:31:23,817
It's just like you said.
We started the war.

1116
01:31:28,455 --> 01:31:32,459
It won't start a war if
nobody hears about it.

1117
01:31:37,831 --> 01:31:41,535
Young people today are
so difficult to control.

1118
01:31:53,047 --> 01:31:54,014
I hate you.

1119
01:31:54,081 --> 01:31:55,115
I hate you!

1120
01:31:55,182 --> 01:31:57,017
I became a vampire
to save you, Steve.

1121
01:31:57,084 --> 01:31:58,385
Thanks.

1122
01:32:12,399 --> 01:32:14,568
Go ahead. Just do it!

1123
01:32:28,048 --> 01:32:29,717
That's enough, boys.

1124
01:32:34,455 --> 01:32:36,623
Steve, come with me.

1125
01:32:37,257 --> 01:32:38,358
Not before
I kick his...

1126
01:32:38,459 --> 01:32:40,394
You will behave!

1127
01:32:41,795 --> 01:32:45,032
It's not time for you to fight. Not yet.

1128
01:32:46,433 --> 01:32:48,469
What does that mean?

1129
01:32:48,569 --> 01:32:50,738
Oh, it's all written
down in a book.

1130
01:32:51,638 --> 01:32:53,974
You do read books,
don't you?

1131
01:33:00,781 --> 01:33:02,015
Steve.

1132
01:33:05,352 --> 01:33:07,154
Look, don't...
Don't go.

1133
01:33:08,822 --> 01:33:11,425
What else am
I supposed to do, man?

1134
01:33:11,492 --> 01:33:13,093
Live with you
and a bunch of freaks?

1135
01:33:14,762 --> 01:33:16,430
It's too late now.

1136
01:33:17,398 --> 01:33:19,466
I have my destiny,
and you have yours.

1137
01:33:20,401 --> 01:33:24,605
How poignant. The parting
of two dear friends.

1138
01:33:25,072 --> 01:33:27,041
Such sweet sorrow.

1139
01:33:28,275 --> 01:33:32,179
Then again, you will
come home to us one day.

1140
01:33:32,880 --> 01:33:35,249
My prodigal son.

1141
01:33:35,315 --> 01:33:39,486
After all, you are
the bloodthirsty one.

1142
01:33:40,454 --> 01:33:45,392
No. Just because I'm a vampire
doesn't mean I'm bloodthirsty.

1143
01:33:47,127 --> 01:33:49,663
It's not about what you are.
It's about who you are.

1144
01:33:58,138 --> 01:33:59,173
Oh.

1145
01:33:59,440 --> 01:34:00,941
I almost forgot.

1146
01:34:50,491 --> 01:34:52,159
Cover yourself.

1147
01:34:54,261 --> 01:34:56,597
You have to teach me
how to do that someday.

1148
01:34:56,597 --> 01:34:59,666
Oh, I'll teach you
everything, son.

1149
01:34:59,733 --> 01:35:05,739
All my gibes and gambols. Now,
ready to go meet your people?

1150
01:35:24,958 --> 01:35:26,226
Bye, Annie.

1151
01:35:34,201 --> 01:35:36,236
Will it work?
Hypnotizing them?

1152
01:35:37,337 --> 01:35:40,941
It works on the memories, but
not on the emotions, not really.

1153
01:35:41,975 --> 01:35:45,245
They'll always feel that
you're still alive, somehow.

1154
01:35:45,579 --> 01:35:47,281
Well, that's good,
right?

1155
01:35:47,381 --> 01:35:48,615
Is it?

1156
01:35:59,393 --> 01:36:01,562
Hey, can I ask
you something?

1157
01:36:04,865 --> 01:36:06,500
Can I kiss you?

1158
01:36:07,568 --> 01:36:12,706
Darren, I let you drink my
blood. Sure, you can kiss me.

1159
01:36:35,462 --> 01:36:38,632
Come on. We don't have all night.
I have an injured spider here.

1160
01:36:41,201 --> 01:36:44,938
All right, how are we going to do
this? I can't carry the both of you.

1161
01:36:46,073 --> 01:36:49,510
You carry Rebecca.
I can flit now.

1162
01:36:49,576 --> 01:36:51,211
Just like a real vampire.

1163
01:36:53,147 --> 01:36:55,916
Oh, Larten, you did it.

1164
01:36:56,417 --> 01:36:58,585
You stuck your
neck out for him.

1165
01:36:58,585 --> 01:37:01,789
You'd think a vampire would know
better than to stick his neck out.

1166
01:37:03,223 --> 01:37:04,925
I am proud of you.

1167
01:37:08,529 --> 01:37:10,631
All those who vote
for making Darren

1168
01:37:10,731 --> 01:37:14,601
a member of the Cirque
raise your hands.

1169
01:37:21,008 --> 01:37:22,376
One hand, Evra.

1170
01:37:22,509 --> 01:37:23,644
Damn it.

1171
01:37:26,080 --> 01:37:28,982
It's done.
He will stay.

1172
01:37:35,122 --> 01:37:36,724
So we get to stay.

1173
01:37:38,392 --> 01:37:40,327
Not for long,
I'm afraid.

1174
01:37:40,627 --> 01:37:42,296
You know, Crepsley,
it's okay.

1175
01:37:45,165 --> 01:37:48,969
It's weird. I spent so much time wishing
that none of this would have happened

1176
01:37:49,036 --> 01:37:53,006
and that we never would have been
to the Cirque in the first place.

1177
01:37:55,008 --> 01:37:58,779
But now I really can't imagine
my life happening any other way.

1178
01:38:02,282 --> 01:38:03,784
Dawn's coming.

1179
01:38:05,018 --> 01:38:08,622
I had something made for
you. It's in your tent.

1180
01:38:08,655 --> 01:38:10,290
A little gift.

1181
01:38:11,892 --> 01:38:14,128
And it's Mr. Crepsley.

1182
01:38:19,233 --> 01:38:22,603
Because you told me to
throw you. Well, I'm sorry.

1183
01:38:24,104 --> 01:38:28,342
You did it, man. Once a
general, always a general.

1184
01:38:28,776 --> 01:38:31,245
I couldn't have
done it better myself.

1185
01:38:31,512 --> 01:38:33,147
At nightfall,
we leave with the boy.

1186
01:38:35,849 --> 01:38:37,551
I suppose we
should tell him.

1187
01:38:38,719 --> 01:38:41,822
No, let's give him one day
to rest. He's earned it.

1188
01:38:44,691 --> 01:38:47,528
Sometimes life does
seem all planned out,

1189
01:38:47,661 --> 01:38:49,296
like there's no choice
in the matter,

1190
01:38:50,264 --> 01:38:51,365
but that's an illusion.

1191
01:38:51,432 --> 01:38:53,133
Speakers. Tasty.

1192
01:38:54,868 --> 01:38:56,503
My name's Darren Shan,

1193
01:38:56,570 --> 01:44:31,972
and I don't just live with a
bunch of freaks. I am one, too.

